problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/subsets/description/
Intuition
Every element in the array presents 2 choices.

include the current element in the subset
exclude the current element from the subset
we explore both possibilities recursively for every index . Once all elements have been processed , the current subset represents one valid answer and is added to the result.

To efficiently explore all combinations , we use backtracking , whenever we choose to include an element we add it to current subset, recursively explore all possibilities , and then remove it before returning. This restores the subset to its previous state so the remaining choices can be explored correctly.

Approach
create 2 lists , resut to store all subsets , temp to store current subset

define a recursive functon dfs(i) where i represents the current index

base case: if i == len(nums) all elements have been considered.
store a copy of temp in result and return

recursive choices: don't take the current element and recurse to the next index.

take the current element by appending it to temp, recurse and then remove it by using pop() to backtrack

start recursion from index 0

